 * Meta Conversions API credentials — TEMPLATE, safe to commit to git.
 *
 * Copy this file to `capi-config.php` (same folder) and fill in your real
 * values. `capi-config.php` is gitignored so your real access token never
 * ends up in version control — same pattern as db.php / admin-config.php.
 *
 * How to get these values:
 *   1. Go to Meta Events Manager (business.facebook.com/events_manager2).
 *   2. Select your pixel (Data Sources > your pixel).
 *   3. Settings tab > "Conversions API" section > "Generate access token".
 *   4. Copy that token below. It does not expire unless you revoke it.
 *
 * If this file is missing or CAPI_ACCESS_TOKEN is left blank, server-side
 * event tracking is silently skipped — the rest of the site keeps working
 * normally, you just won't get the ad-blocker-resistant tracking this
 * enables. The browser-side Meta Pixel (in index.html / blog-layout.php)
 * keeps working either way.
 */

